<author><name><![CDATA[kik]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-01-07T16:59:39-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-01-07T16:59:39-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26&amp;p=56#p56</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26&amp;p=56#p56"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Windows 8 home screen permanent choice]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26&amp;p=56#p56"><![CDATA[
Ok. I get your point. Sorry for taking your time with such weirdo requests.<br />I was just hoping for some way to avoid being constantly shuffled by the OS between the Modern Start Screen and the Desktop mode, arbitrarily based on which type of app was last run, each time having to click somewhere to get back to the screen I want to see. Aren't you annoyed when you are in that new modern start screen, using several new apps with the new look, and then just by running calculator, the whole desktop appears and you have to click again in the corner to get back to the modern start screen, even after closing the calculator or other classic apps?<br /> <br />To me both are useful interfaces, but they don't mix well together and have different usage (touch vs mouse). So it would make sense at least that each screen would correspond to a user selectable mode:<br />If I'm on a tablet I normally don't want to see the desktop, and if I work with a mouse I'd usually not want the Modern Start Screen.<br /> <br />I guess we'll have to wait until most applications are converted to Windows 8 apps to have a more coherent user experience... But right now not even all Microsoft accessories are available as Windows 8 apps.<br />So until that's the case, many users will stick to desktop mode with Classic Shell and rarely even touch the new Windows 8 apps.<br /> <br />Thanks again. Best regards and keep up the good work.<br /> <br />kik<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">kik</a> — Mon Jan 07, 2013 4:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
