<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Windows 8 home screen permanent choice]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26&amp;p=54#p54"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">kik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />option 1: supposing it's possible to detect if the Modern Start Screen is currently opened, always go back to the Modern Start Screen in this case.<br />or option 2: supposing it's possible to detect if the Desktop is currently opened, always go back to the Desktop Screen in this case.<br /></div>I don't understand - if the Modern Start Screen is already opened, there is nowhere to go - you are already there. Same with the Desktop.<br />Either way, any such discussion is just theoretical, because there is no way to detect when an application exits. Not without some serious hooking into the OS anyway.<br />Also, you are assuming a very trivial usage - open application, use it, close it. In practice people run multiple applications simultaneously and close them in arbitrary order. That seriously complicates things.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Mon Jan 07, 2013 4:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
