<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=26&amp;p=53#p53"><![CDATA[
Hi, thanks for your quick reply.<br /> <br />Well, maybe a simpler approach would be possible providing a similar solution:<br /><br />option 1: supposing it's possible to detect if the Modern Start Screen is currently opened, always go back to the Modern Start Screen in this case.<br />or option 2: supposing it's possible to detect if the Desktop is currently opened, always go back to the Desktop Screen in this case.<br /><br />An even more radical approach would be a permanent user choice: either always go back to Modern Screen / or always go back to Desktop Screen.<br />In that case, there would be no need to detect anything; the user preferred &quot;home screen&quot; would always be launched or displayed when no other app is on screen.<br />But then, would it still be possible to explicitely launch the desktop or Modern Start Screen without weird side effects!?<br /><br />Gee, I'm not sure my post is very clear. Sorry if it's not.<br /><br />kik<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">kik</a> — Mon Jan 07, 2013 4:02 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
